Theory Answers
1. Why Canary Fails with Information Leak?
If attacker leaks memory:
•	Canary value becomes known 
•	Attacker overwrites buffer AND restores correct canary 
•	Protection bypassed 
________________________________________
2. NX/DEP Bypass Technique
Attackers use:
Return-Oriented Programming
ROP reuses existing executable code snippets ("gadgets") instead of injecting shellcode.
________________________________________
3. PIE and ASLR
Without PIE:
•	Main binary address stays fixed 
•	Only stack/heap randomized 
With PIE:
•	Entire executable randomized 
•	Stronger ASLR 
Compile with PIE:
gcc -fPIE -pie -o aslr_pie aslr_test.c
